description:
Mr. Shawn Koh, corporate leader turned entrepreneur, is the founder of I.O.T. Workz, a Smart Nation ambassador, offering integrated IoT solutions for residential, commercial, industrial and government services.

He developed the first predictive online-data reduction system for a military data center to provide real-time health monitoring and alert when he was with the RSAF in 1996. Between 2003 and 2006, he formed the Ground-Based Radar System team in ST Electronics (InfoSoft) to provide software maintenance for all radar systems in Singapore. During his tenure with SGX from 2007 to 2018, Shawn hold multiple portfolios and delivered many large-scale projects with his team.
 
Currently, in I.O.T. Workz, Shawn and his team delivers IoT solutions such as wheelchair tracking systems for hospital, environment monitoring and alert system for medical centers, industrial IoT for contract manufacturing engineering and many other innovation initiatives. 

Mr. Shawn Koh holds a Master Degree in Technopreneurship and Innovation from Nanyang Technological University, an ACTA certified trainer that provides IoT and AI related training and appointed as a Technical Committee member for ITE Work-Study Diploma.

description:
CEO and Strategist-General Charles leads Solaris Consortium of Management Consultancies to provide strategy and cross functional consulting to underserved governments, corporates and nonprofits (trisectors) with emphasis on complex problem solving where the problem may even be ill-defined, involves trisector players, needs an Agile approach towards tight strategy-tech-ops-org dev integration.

Trisector strategist-entrepreneur-innovation specialist with 20 years of contributions in government (4 start ups), civil society (8 start ups). Pracademic-adjunct faculty in university applied problem solving programs in Singapore (NUS NTU SMU), Civil Service College, and Swiss (St Gallen) covering urban-tech, social-tech, policy, business and trisector themed strategy and innovation. 

Doctorates in public policy, corporate strategy (soon), strategy education (started)
Degrees in international relations, education, accounting, security management, and law (soon). 
Executive education in strategy-innovation-entrepreneurship-sustainability-marketing from functional best from B schools: Harvard, Cambridge, Oxford, MIT, Stanford, Wharton, INSEAD, LBS, Babson, Kellogg, Berkeley. 
Passion in smart+sustainability city development, learning from component best from: Delft TU, EFPL, Harvard, MIT, Manchester, Cambridge, Oxford, Imperial, IBM.

Internationally certified management consultant, certified competent facilitator, project management professional, agile-certified practitioner, DevOpsLeader, SAFe 5 program consultant, Charles fuses the best of academia and practitioner worlds in his consulting practice with emphasis on complex problems such as sector-transformation, internationalisation of SMEs, social impact and sustainability. 

Charles has taught officials, and postgraduates in international affairs and public policy, and was Fulbright fellow at Brookings Institution and non resident senior fellow at East-West Institute (New York). He is founding editor for Routledge series on Strategy, Wisdom and Skills.

Charles presides at Association for Public Affairs (empowers youth in policy discourses and action), and curated SG100 Compass movement, government-led Singapore Model Parliament and Cabinet series as chief judge since 2015, and co-curated Youth Action Challenge for government. He is the youngest elected member of Scout Council, country co-lead for Swiss Stars alumni Singapore and country rep for Institute of Certified Management Accountants.

Charles seeks to create and apply knowledge to practice in service of the greater public good.

description:
In his two decades in the business world, Luke has guided and assisted hundreds of businesses and leaders to improve business performance by aligning people, technology and process to create better outcomes. 

He does this using a ground-up approach, and by identifying bottlenecks and inefficiencies then implementing actionable plans. Specialising in helping technical experts to become great leaders by letting go of 'doing' and empowering their people to thrive. 
 
Luke believes that every success story is built on outcomes from a solid foundation of customer understanding, proven business strategies, and highly disciplined attention to detail. His mission is to enable organisations to unlock their true potential through great people and technology. He uses his years of experience as an entrepreneur, consultant and executive to help them do so in the shortest time possible.  
 
In 2004, Luke co-founded Mercury IT, a business that has been in continuous operation since and won several awards along the way. Early in his career, Luke realised that the recipe for success had multiple ingredients. Being ‘good at what you do’ is just one of them. He decided to invest every second of his free time to broaden his horizons, develop new skills, and learn more about finance, marketing strategies, sales techniques, and customer behaviour. 
 
Luke transitioned from executive to non-executive director of Mercury in 2017 to complete his Master of Business Administration. While completing his MBA, he was appointed Chief Information Officer (CIO) of Australia Pacific Airport Corporation (incorporating Melbourne and Launceston airports), the second-largest airport operator in Australia. He led the transformation of the corporation’s IT business into a value-aligned strategic partner within the business, by developing cost optimisations, improving customer service, and reducing IT risks.
 
Luke now works with clients globally to enable them to achieve more by unlocking the potential of their people and technology.

description:
I thrive under stress. I love to overcome challenges with unique innovations. My cup of tea is to plan and execute a blue ocean strategy, often with the use of computational or engineering innovations.

I have been an enigma all my life…

- The inaugural nuclear scholar from Singapore, whose limited land area inhibits reactor siting.
- The scientist who rode a motorcycle in winter from Cambridge to London.
- The graduate student who drove across the British Channelfrom Right Hand Drive UK to Left Hand Drive France in a 20 year old Citroen. 
- The geek who dances semi-professionally and plays in a band.
- The physics graduate who learnt about crystals, uranium chemistry, nuclear energy, high performance computing, artificial intelligence and this is probably the beginning!
- The C-Suite who puts his team above himself. 
 
And I still have a long way to go. 

I have taught and spoken at top academic institutions like NUS, Singapore Science Centre, Goldschmidt- Paris, Cambridge University, Oxford University and Australian- ANSTO on a wide variety of topics ranging from nuclear physics to computer engineering. I am also an associate at many organisations such as Fellow of Geological Society, London, The Oxford and Cambridge Society of Singapore, Society of Medical Physicists (Singapore).

As Chief Scientist of Carro, I lead all aspects of technological innovations in 4 countries in Southeast Asia – Singapore, Indonesia, Thailand and Malaysia. This includes the wide use of data analytics/ statistics, data science, algorithms, machine learning in the domain of data visualisation computer vision, acoustic analysis, behavioural analytics, engineering and IOT innovation. These are mainly based on Python, C/C++ and Java. 

Here at Carro, we leverage technology to debut several “Singapore’s first” technological innovations like: 

- First Usage-based insurance by using Telematics
- First Contactless Car viewing. 
- First Computer Vision model to analyse defects in cars
and many more (patent pending). 

We are recruiting a team of young, enthusiastic data scientists and engineers to join us in this endeavour to make Carro the #1 AI-Driven Used Car Marketplace in Asia.

description:
I am currently a second-year undergraduate in Singapore Management University (SMU), pursuing a degree in Information Systems (Smart City Management and Technology Major), with a second major in Business Analytics. I am expecting to graduate in May 2023. 

As an outgoing individual, I chose to strike a strong work-life balance in SMU. I am eager in my pursuit of knowledge, especially within the field of my degree, Information Systems. I also currently serve as the Music Director of SMU's resident Afro-Brazilian percussion band. Learning to maintain a healthy GPA while juggling such external commitments has allowed me to grow into a driven and detail-focused individual. 

As someone who has always found quantitative subjects such as Math and Science to be my forte, pursuing a degree in Information Systems has been second nature to me as my strong points complement the skills required to excel in this field. I have chosen to pursue the Smart-City Management and Technology Major because i see the value in not only constraining myself in the Business IT sector, but harnessing such technologies to deliver innovative solutions and services to improve the lives of citizens in society.
